<comment type="function">
<text evidence="4">Bifunctional protein comprised of a catalytic subunit and a regulatory subunit. The catalytic subunit of cellulose synthase polymerizes uridine 5'-diphosphate glucose to cellulose in a processive way. The thick cellulosic mats generated by this enzyme probably provide a specialized protective environment to the bacterium. The regulatory subunit binds bis-(3'-5') cyclic diguanylic acid (c-di-GMP).</text>
</comment>
